{"parse":{"title":"The Megas","pageid":16006995,"revid":684475042,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\">This article is about the mini-series comic. For the US-based video-game rock band, see <a href=\"/wiki/The_Megas_(band)\" title=\"The Megas (band)\">The Megas (band)</a>.</div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:152px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Megas_-1.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/5/5f/Megas_-1.jpg/150px-Megas_-1.jpg\" width=\"150\" height=\"225\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/5/5f/Megas_-1.jpg/225px-Megas_-1.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/5/5f/Megas_-1.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"258\" data-file-height=\"387\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Megas_-1.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><i>The Megas #1</i><br />Art by <a href=\"/wiki/Peter_Rubin\" title=\"Peter Rubin\">Peter Rubin</a></div></div></div>\n<p><i><b>The Megas</b></i> is a 5-issue mini-series from <a href=\"/wiki/Virgin_Comics\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Virgin Comics\">Virgin Comics</a> and film director <a href=\"/wiki/Jonathan_Mostow\" title=\"Jonathan Mostow\">Jonathan Mostow</a> (<a href=\"/wiki/Terminator_3:_Rise_of_the_Machines\" title=\"Terminator 3: Rise of the Machines\">Terminator 3: Rise of the Machines</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/U-571_(film)\" title=\"U-571 (film)\">U-571</a>).  Mostow is already reported to be developing the property into a feature film.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Credits\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Credits</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Plot\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Plot</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Publication\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Publication</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Credits\">Credits</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Megas&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Credits\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The Megas was created by <a href=\"/wiki/Jonathan_Mostow\" title=\"Jonathan Mostow\">Jonathan Mostow</a>, and is written by <a href=\"/wiki/John_Harrison\" title=\"John Harrison\">John Harrison</a>, with art by <a href=\"/wiki/Peter_Rubin\" title=\"Peter Rubin\">Peter Rubin</a> and color by <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=S._Periaswamy&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"S. Periaswamy (page does not exist)\">S. Periaswamy</a>.  The story is by Mostow and Harrison.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Plot\">Plot</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Megas&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Plot\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The Megas explores what might have happened had the founding fathers of the United States established another aristocracy rather than a democracy.  The eponymous Megas are the elite members of the American Royalty, a somewhat benevolent but dictatorial ruling class.  Now, in the 21st Century, the Megas have ruled <a href=\"/wiki/United_States\" title=\"United States\">America</a> for over 200 years.  Mostow described the story for <a href=\"/wiki/Variety_(magazine)\" title=\"Variety (magazine)\">Variety</a>:\n</p>\n<blockquote><p>The story \"revolves around Detective Jack Madison and his race-against-the-clock investigation to uncover secrets behind the mysterious sex-fueled suicide of a Prince in The Megas royal family. Meanwhile, the King is on his deathbed at The White Palace (yes, at 1600 Pennsylvania Avenue!), and society is bracing for the inevitable chaos that will surely ensue once he dies.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Publication\">Publication</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Megas&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Publication\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The first issue debuted on February 27, 2008.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Megas&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.darkhorizons.com/news08/080227a.php\">Mostow Adapting His \"Megas\" Comic (February 27th 2008)</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.cinematical.com/2008/02/28/virgin-prepares-the-megas-for-the-big-screen\">Virgin Prepares 'The Megas' For the Big Screen - Cinematical</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Megas&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.comicbookresources.com/news/newsitem.cgi?id=13170\">Mostow talks \"The Megas\" at Virgin Comics</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Comic_Book_Resources\" title=\"Comic Book Resources\">Comic Book Resources</a>, February 28, 2008</li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://forum.newsarama.com/showthread.php?t=148562\">Jonathan Mostow talks about <i>The Megas</i></a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Newsarama\" title=\"Newsarama\">Newsarama</a>, February 29, 2008</li></ul>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Comiclogo.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/48/Comiclogo.svg/32px-Comiclogo.svg.png\" width=\"32\" height=\"33\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/48/Comiclogo.svg/48px-Comiclogo.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/48/Comiclogo.svg/64px-Comiclogo.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"106\" data-file-height=\"109\" /></a></td><td><i>This <a href=\"/wiki/Comics\" title=\"Comics\">comics</a>-related article is a <a href=\"/wiki/Wik